Text: Introductions. How am I, I am keeping well thank you. My name is Tony Millner. How old am I, I am in my late 50s. I live in a city; the city is called Birmingham.

Reason for visit. The reason I have come for a sight test today, what brings me along, why I am here today, is because I've noticed my distance vision is no longer as good as it was, and I don't have any glasses for my distance vision. My distance vision has been getting worse over the last couple of years. I wonder if distance glasses might help me see more clearly. I do however wear glasses for reading. I've been wearing reading glasses for the past 15 years and I can read well with them. That is what brings me along today, this is why I am here, this is what brought me along, I am here, my because distance vision is not so good, I'd like your help to get some glasses!

Other symptoms. For the past year now I've been getting dull headaches, on and off, on the side of my head, around once a week, when doing computer work or reading for long periods of time. The headaches dont really bother me too much but they can be a little annoying. I find that taking regular breaks from the computer screen and reading helps. I have to use my reading glasses when using the computer. Luckily, I don't get any eyestrain, but the headaches are getting annoying. I don't get any double vision or floaters in my vision but for several years I've been getting flashes of light in my vision every night. I am not sure if the flashing lights are in both eyes or just one. The flashing lights happen when I get up in the night to go to the loo, they just last a second or two. I am not worried about the flashing lights, they are no big deal.

Last eye examination and optical correction. My last eye test was about 3 years ago. I think my reading glasses are a little older than that, I can't quite remember. My reading glasses could be 5 years old now, I'm not entirely sure exactly. I dont have any spare reading glasses and if I lost these I would be really stuck. I first started wearing reading glasses when I was about 45 years old. I dont wear contact lenses. I dont want to try contact lenses. I don't have distance glasses. I don't have bifocals. I don't have varifocals. I only have reading glasses.

My ocular history and my previous eye problems. I have had problems with my eyes in the past, previously, about 30 years ago I had a cyst removed from an eye lid, it was like a little surgery. When I was discharged from the hospital, I was prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis. That was the only time I went to an eye hospital. I don't get any eye pain. I don't experience any burning sensations in my eyes. I don't get much redness but sometimes my eyes feel dry. I never had my eyes patched. These are the problems I have had with my eyes in the past.

Family ocular and medical history. My family don't have any health problems, like diabetes or high blood pressure. My family are pretty healthy as far as I know. Regarding eyes, in my family, my dad had cataracts. The only eye problem in my family has been cataract. My parents used to wear reading glasses.

My general health. My general health is good. I don't have diabetes, but my doctor told me I am probably genetically predisposed to type 2 diabetes.  My last medical exam was 2 months ago to get my blood sugar levels checked.

My medication. I take vitamin D and cod liver oil supplements but no medication like pills or tablets. Around May/ June time I may take antihistamines and sometimes steroid drops if my hayfever really flares up. These are the medications I may take. I don't smoke since I know it's damaging to my health. I drink a gin and tonic every night, its my little helper!

My occupation and hobbies. For a living, work, I am a secondary school teacher. I teach biology. I really enjoy teaching biology. I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen since I'm a teacher. I also spend too long on my mobile phone, I would say about 2 hours a day. I am a driver, it's easy for me to drive up to the school I work at mostly by car but sometimes I even motorcycle. My hobbies are motorcycling, drawing and climbing on the weekends! I climb on sea cliffs around South Wales and do the occasional trip to the Alps. Last year I went to Spain on my motorcycle with my partner, we had a great time. I've only recently taken up drawing, mostly faces, its a nice way to relax.
Anything else. If possible I would like to have distance glasses but I would also be interested in getting some spare reading glasses.
